🩺 🦊 ABOUT US 🦊🩺
Hello! I’m Natalie and I’m an oncologist (cancer physician) in the Seattle area. While many adventure accounts are full time travelers or work remote jobs, I share PNW gems with more than a full time schedule, hence the name “Adventures on Call.”
.
Nike is a sheltie mix (aka “freckled fox”). I got her as a puppy during my Internal Medicine residency and lucked out that she’s the world’s most easygoing dog and a great traveler.
.
When I’m not treating cancer patients in the hospital, I love hiking, baking for my foodblog @obsessivecooking, and photographing. So if you love dogs, travel/hiking, and desserts, we’re going to be great friends.
.
======================
.
🏔️WHAT YOU’LL FIND HERE 🏔️
• Everyday adventures in the PNW for busy people - resources, reviews, and guides for weekend and PTO
• Dog friendly hikes and places
• Tips for outdoor family fun
• Cozy cabins, unique stays, airbnbs
• Life as a cancer physician, our convoluted US healthcare system, and navigating work / life balance
.
======================
.
🌲 WHY I DO THIS🌲
While I have my dream job as a cancer physician, photography/instagram is my passion project. Traveling the world, being in nature, and enjoying new experiences is my way to cope with a very high stress job. “Nature itself is the best physician” - Hippocrates
.
Cancer has a way of reminding us that life is short. Adventure doesn’t have to be big to be meaningful. My life is full, and I have many adventures beyond the traditional definition of hiking/outdoor activities.
.
My goal is to share the best PNW experiences, and show that even non-influencer people with regular in-office jobs can still go on adventures locally.

I hope the resources and tips on our page inspire you to explore the PNW with dogs / kids. Life is meant to be lived 🌅
.
❓Where are you located and how did you find us? Welcome to all the new faces and old friends

Hi! We changed our IG name - welcome to @adventuresoncall!
.
To streamline my life, I’m consolidating Nike’s @hungrynike and my @adventuresoncall instagrams since they overlap so much. (I will still be baking at my foodblog @obsessivecooking. So if you love dogs, travel/hiking, and desserts, we’re going to be great friends)
.
I made a separate personal/photography account originally to share more than just “dog IG account.” So much has changed since Nike - no more long distance marriage, having my daughters, moving all over the country for our medical training, and wrapping up my >10 year long journey of becoming a cancer physician
.
My life is full, and I have many adventures beyond the traditional definition of hiking/outdoor activities. This name allows me to evolve with whatever future life changes may happen, but I know art and medicine will always be a part of me.
.
Don’t worry, this account will stay Nike/dog focused, because she’s the star honestly (and no one else in the family is a willing model lol). Ultimately, photography, storytelling, and capturing memories will be the heart of what I do
.
Thanks for sticking around as I share my loves. (And if you have any questions on this process, feel free to ask)
.
.
.

✈️This is NOT Provence, France. This is not even in Europe.
📍This is Washington (🪻+ 🏔️)
.
👋🏻 More everyday PNW adventures for busy people @adventuresoncall
.
☀️ Did you know that lavender is a huge industry in Washington, even though lavender likes very dry, hot weather?
.
💜The PNW is infamous for rain, but there are unique microclimates (mild winters, low precipitation, abundant sunshine) which is perfect for lavender cultivation. In fact, Sequim is the Lavender Capital of North America
.
🪻Peak Lavender blooming season is now! Blooms are late June through early August
🪻 This year’s Sequim Lavender Festival is July 18 - July 20, 2025 (Personally I prefer other days for less crowds)
🪻 Places to find lavender farms include Sequim, Whidbey Island, Ferndale, Olympia, and Woodinville
🪻Sequim Lavender Trail is a scenic driving / cycling route on a tour of the lavender farms in Sequim open all summer long.
🪻Check for U-pick and dog friendly options (many are dog friendly)! 🐾
🪻 Many lavender farms have stores open all year - highly recommend trying lavender ice cream, lavender lemonade, lavender jam, lavender soaps/lotions, and more 🍦
.
🏔️And you can get lavender + Mt Rainier views on a clear day
.
.
.

Everyone is or knows someone affected by cancer. It’s a matter of when, not if. 🩺 if you have a story about cancer and healthcare, please share below
.
Hi, I’m a photographer foremost on @adventuresoncall, and I’m also a medical oncology physician. I just want to highlight what my cancer patients face and what it’s like for those working in healthcare.
.
The impact of these sweeping cuts to Medicaid will reach everyone, not just in cancer but especially in primary care, ER, geriatric care, women’s health, and pediatrics
.
.
.
.
(All thoughts are my own and not of my employer)

🍓 Part 1 What a Washington Summer Tastes Like Series: Strawberries 🍓
.
📍 Welcome to my Eating in the PNW Guide. These two farms are in Snohomish, just 30 min from Seattle. 
.
👋🏻Sharing local farms and more PNW adventures @adventuresoncall. Stay tuned for more in the series!
.
☀️In the PNW, strawberry season kicks off the start of summer in June—and we make the most of it. This season, we picked over 30 lbs of strawberries! While the strawberry season just ended, there’s still plenty of U-pick for Summer
.
🧺Whether you’re out with kids, meeting up with friends, or just craving a little nostalgia, U-pick farms are one of the simplest ways to slow down and savor the season.
.
📍Bailey Farm (Snohomish, WA) – Open June - October 
•  A charming family-run farm (5 generations)
•  Mountain views, easy rows for kids, and beautiful picnic spots
•  In addition to strawberries, they also have Upick vegetables, raspberries, flowers, apples, corn and pumpkins!
.
📍Swans Trail Farms (Snohomish, WA) – Open June - October 
•  Bigger fields, great variety of attractions, and lots of space to roam. 
•  In addition to strawberries they have Upick apples and pumpkins
•  Farmer camp, activities for kids (ziplines, tractor rides, slides, ropes course, etc), cidery
•  Baby animals and strawberries Festival in June and Harvest Festival Sept- October
•  Plus: cider donuts. Enough said.
.
.

Stay tuned for more local picks in this series as we eat our way through the PNW—one summer flavor at a time. 🌿
.
.
.

📍 BUCKETLIST WASHINGTON CALENDAR - BY MONTH 📍 For local Washingtons and out-of-state visitors planning a trip, there’s so much to do each month 🌲🥾🏔️
.
More everyday PNW adventures for busy people @adventuresoncall
.

• Bavarian Icefest in Leavenworth
• Leavenworth Reindeer farm
.
FEBRUARY
• Romantic weekend at Cozy A frame cabin
• Shuck oysters at a glamping resort
• Snowshoe at Artist Point and Gold Creek
.
MARCH
• Daffodil Bloom in La Conner

🌲🥾🚲 POV: You want to raise confident, curious kids who love the outdoors—but you’re not sure where to start. 🌲🥾🚲
.
We’ve been there. It can feel overwhelming to get little ones off screens and into nature—especially when the whining starts 5 minutes into a walk.
.
But here’s what we’ve learned: the right tools make all the difference.
.
Just over a year ago, Izzy sat on a balance bike for the first time. One month later, she was pedaling on 2 wheels and has been flying on her woom bike since. Izzy has grown from a woom 2 to a woom 3, letting her go on bigger adventures!
.
@woombikesusa are ultra-lightweight, built just for kids, and help them feel in control from the very first ride. The result? More confidence, more independence—and a lot more time outside.
.
We’re not raising perfect kids; we’re raising outdoor explorers. More laughter, more scraped knees, more dirty shoes, more unforgettable memories.
.
Less screen time. More green time. Ride Woom. 🌲💛🚲
.

🏞️ 🐾 Your Easiest PNW Weekend Getaway - Has EVERYTHING - No Planning/No Stress 🏞️ 🐾
• Not a hotel. Not a cabin. Something better. Just 90 min from Seattle, but it feels like a total reset. ☀️Suncadia has something for everyone
.
👋🏻 More everyday PNW for busy people who work regular jobs @adventuresoncall
.
Here’s everything you can do at this dog- and kid-friendly resort:
.
✨ FAMILY FRIENDLY ADVENTURES: 
• Splash in the outdoor & indoor pools, with water slides!
• Roast marshmallows at the community firepits (unlimited free smores each night!)
• Explore over 40 miles of paved + wooded trails
• Join seasonal events like outdoor movies, crafts, & festivals 
• Hit the playgrounds + open green spaces for free play 
• Bike scenic forest trails or bike pump track (rentals available onsite)
• Visit Nelson Farm
.
🐶 DOG FRIENDLY HIGHLIGHTS:
• Pet-welcoming lodging (cabins, condos & lodge rooms)
• Dog-friendly hiking and walking trails
• Riverside romps and wooded off-leash areas
• Patio dining at dog-friendly spots like The Stovehouse
.
🌲 RELAXATION & WELLNESS: 
• Book a massage or facial at the Glade Spring Spa
• Relax in the outdoor mineral springs at Glade Spring Spa
• Sip coffee on the cabin deck with views of the Cle Elum River
• Soak in a hot tub under the stars
• Steam/sauna to recharge
• Yoga + fitness classes + gym
.
🍷 FOOD & GROWN UP FUN:
• Enjoy cocktails and mountain views at the Source in the Lodge
• Wine tasting locally
• Local beer flights, cozy bars, and in-room s’mores kits
• Golf, axe throwing, and seasonal rentals (snowshoes to paddleboards)
.
🧳 PERFECT FOR: Weekend getaways • Family adventures • Multigenerational trips • Dog parents • Nature lovers • Spa days • Outdoor birthdays or celebrations
.

🪻🏔️ EASY MICROADVENTURES - Lupines + Mt Rainier + the best local coffeeshop 🏔️🪻
Fields of purple and mountain views and coffee —this local trail is quintessential PNW
.
👋🏻 More everyday PNW for busy people who work regular jobs @adventuresoncall.
.
😩I’m going to be honest, I woke up at 4am TWICE on my precious weekends to try catch Mt Rainier on a clear sunrise here, but despite the Apple weather app saying clear skies, the clouds completely covered Mt Rainier.
😤This is why I’m sharing this reel later in the season. But this is the reality of being a photographer/content creator who also has to work a regular job and bring her kids to school. Ah, next time
.
 🪻 Van Lierop Park:🛝
• Lupine fields bloom late May to early June
• Paved, stroller-friendly walkway
• New barn themed playground opening end of June 2025!
• Great for kids, scooters, and slow walks
• Leashed dog-friendly 🐾
• Spot Mount Rainier peeking through on clear days
• Links up with the Foothills Trail for longer adventures
.
☕ Fika Coffee House (just 2 min away):🥐
• Cozy Scandinavian-inspired café with calm, modern vibes
• Lavender lattes, cardamom buns, & baked-from-scratch pastries (highly recommend the almond croissant!)
• Outdoor seating that’s pup-friendly 🐶
• Friendly staff and seriously good coffee (cuban coffee and honey lattes are local favorites)
• Perfect warm-up or wind-down after your walk
.
🏔️Why I love this combo:🥾
• Quick, easy, and full of joy
• Wildflowers + coffee = therapy
• Kid and dog-friendly (future playground opening end of June 2025)
.
📍Van Lierop Park + Fika Coffee – Puyallup, WA
.
.
I think it first saw this park from @flawvorful and @suitcasesinseattle years ago, check them out for good local recs
.

📍Save this cute mountain town for your next getaway! Things to do/stay/eat - Ultimate Leavenworth Weekend Itinerary 🏔️🥾🌲
.
👋🏻 More everyday PNW for busy people who work regular jobs @adventuresoncall
.
🚗Just 2.5 hrs from Seattle, Leavenworth is one of my favorite weekend trips - from charming boutiques to riverside stays, here’s how to spend the perfect weekend in this Bavarian mountain town:
.
STROLL + SHOP DOWNTOWN LEAVENWORTH
🛍️Check out Kris Kringl, Posy Handpicked Goods, A Book For All Seasons, Paprika, and Wurlygigz for the cutest local finds.
🪗 Catch live music, art exhibits, or a festival in the village square
🏔️  Enjoy the epic mountain views
.
THINGS TO DO + EXPLORE
🎁 Tour the quirky Nutcracker Museum - one of the largest collections in the world
🦌 Feed and pet reindeer at the Leavenworth Reindeer Farm  (come in late spring to see the baby reindeer)
🛶Paddle or picnic at Lake Wenatchee
.
STAY
🛌 Cozy up at the dreamy Riverfront Chalet, the cutest airbnb
🌲 Peaceful and private location with a beautiful river
🔥 Enjoy the firepit for smores, outdoor deck, and wood burning stove
.
EAT AND DRINK
🥨 München Haus for brats, pretzels, & beer
🍕 Leavenworth Pizza Co. for casual family vibes
🍻 Blewett Brewing & Blitzen Brew for craft beer lovers - try the cider flight
🍪 Gingerbread Factory for treats that taste like nostalgia
🍦 Whistlepunk for ice cream - get the ice cream flight
🌭Blitzen Brew for reindeer sausage and strawberry potato lefse
.
Tag and share with someone who needs a little Bavarian escape (that’s an easy weekend drive) ✨
.
.
.

TIPS
✨ Don’t forget to wash your fruit before eating them - I’ve seen worms and bugs inside
✨ U pick fruit has a shorter shelf life (picked at peak ripeness/no preservatives) - eat quickly
✨ Pick a bunch, and freeze the rest. Cheaper than buying at the grocery (especially blackberries)
✨ Pick up after your pup and keep them on leash! Let’s keep the few dog friendly farms dog friendly 🐾
